headline: Why Berkshire, Coca-Cola, and Other Low-Volatility Stocks Are Killing It in 2025
summary: The stock market has been on a wild ride in 2025, giving stocks that tend to sit out bouts of volatility a chance to shine.  The outperformance represents a turnaround from 2023 and 2024, when the stock market was marching steadily upward, leaving staid, low-volatility shares behind.  The  exchange-traded fund has returned 4.1%, beating the broad market by more than five percentage points.
